    "text": "Slot it as an easier fourth day, not a clone of the other three. With three hard lifting days, the version of a fourth that tends to stick is a lighter session, think accessory work, technique practice or easy conditioning, placed so you never stack it directly before your heaviest day. A common shape is hard, easy, hard, rest, hard, easy-fourth, rest, but fit it to your spreadsheet's split. Worth being upfront: the only data I have on you is manually logged sleep, 7.3 hours last night, which is decent, so I can't see how you're absorbing your current three days. Run the new structure for three weeks, and if your logged sleep stays steady and the big lifts keep moving normally, the fourth day has earned its slot.",
